1
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:39,999
=The Litchi Road=

2
00:01:40,020 --> 00:01:42,980
(Osmanthus of the Old Mansion: Two)

3
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:47,900
(February of the 13th year of Tianbao,
Chang'an)

4
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:55,520
Father, when will you

5
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:57,066
take me to see the old mansion?

6
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,120
I've been busy

7
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:02,430
with work lately.

8
00:03:07,470 --> 00:03:09,030
I'll give you the key.

9
00:03:10,310 --> 00:03:11,150
Later,

10
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,755
pass it on to your uncle.

11
00:03:16,310 --> 00:03:17,430
When he's back,

12
00:03:17,430 --> 00:03:18,622
have him take you there.

13
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,240
Here you go.

14
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:23,990
When will Uncle be back?

15
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,800
Maybe in three to five days.

16
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,030
What if he doesn't come back?

17
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:33,280
Why not?

18
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:34,840
Just like you,

19
00:03:35,430 --> 00:03:36,910
he was born and raised in Chang'an.

20
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,400
Chang'an is his home.

21
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:41,040
If he can't make it back...

22
00:03:44,560 --> 00:03:45,711
If he can't make it back...

23
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,240
Ouch!

24
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,080
Are you all right?

25
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,520
The breakfast you made is really salty.

26
00:04:02,177 --> 00:04:03,430
I didn't use that much salt.

27
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:04,555
I added a lot of vinegar.

28
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,750
Father,

29
00:04:06,750 --> 00:04:08,360
I wasn't eating slowly on purpose.

30
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,190
It really didn't taste good.

31
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,750
I didn't blame you.

32
00:04:12,000 --> 00:04:12,910
I just think

33
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:14,711
you should learn to tie your hair.

34
00:04:14,910 --> 00:04:16,800
I can. I'm just slow.

35
00:04:17,070 --> 00:04:18,190
Father, slow down a bit.

36
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,310
Slow down?

37
00:04:19,310 --> 00:04:20,000
You walk faster.

38
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,680
I have to report for duty,

39
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:22,920
and there's a lot of other work.

40
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:23,977
I'm running out of time.

41
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:26,070
Then why did you ask me

42
00:04:26,070 --> 00:04:27,070
to tie my hair just now?

43
00:04:27,360 --> 00:04:28,430
Now my hair looks bad,

44
00:04:28,466 --> 00:04:30,040
and you're mad that you're running late.

45
00:04:30,422 --> 00:04:31,000
I just think

46
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,466
everything has to start somewhere.

47
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,680
When I leave

48
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,040
for work later,

49
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:36,870
you'll have to

50
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:39,555
sweep, do your laundry, and cook
all by yourself, right?

51
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,000
You're hurting me.

52
00:04:41,510 --> 00:04:42,720
I can go to school by myself.

53
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,070
You can?

54
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:45,800
I know the way.

55
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:48,466
Didn't you say everything has to
start somewhere?

56
00:04:48,630 --> 00:04:50,190
Aren't you already late for duty?

57
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,560
Did you see

58
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:54,870
a girl this tall?

59
00:05:55,955 --> 00:05:57,270
I don't understand.

60
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,040
Did you see

61
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:02,270
a girl this tall?

62
00:06:02,270 --> 00:06:03,160
She was walking alone.

63
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,720
Is your child missing?

64
00:06:14,830 --> 00:06:16,600
Xiu'er.

65
00:06:17,888 --> 00:06:19,290
What happened? Why are you anxious?

66
00:06:19,390 --> 00:06:20,600
What happened, Shande?

67
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,377
What's going on?

68
00:06:21,422 --> 00:06:23,040
Did you see Xiu'er come back?

69
00:06:23,190 --> 00:06:23,830
No.

70
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:24,670
She's gone missing?

71
00:06:24,880 --> 00:06:25,720
Where's Xiu'er?

72
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,800
I looked away, and she disappeared.

73
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,800
- Look for her.
- Let's go.

74
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,360
Yes, right.

75
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,200
Xiu'er!

76
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:33,030
Xiu'er!

77
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:41,750
You scared me.

78
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:43,190
Why did you come here?

79
00:06:46,630 --> 00:06:47,680
You had me so scared.

80
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:51,390
I thought someone took you.

81
00:06:51,511 --> 00:06:52,822
I was looking for you everywhere.

82
00:06:53,630 --> 00:06:54,470
You really scared me.

83
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,000
Father,

84
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,120
while I was walking,

85
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,088
I thought of you leaving me all alone

86
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:04,040
in Chang'an for work,
I suddenly felt so lonely.

87
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:06,830
So I thought if I came
to the old mansion,

88
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:09,422
Mother would be here for me.

89
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,440
Father,

90
00:07:14,040 --> 00:07:15,244
you're not mad at me, are you?

91
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,400
No, I'm not.

92
00:07:18,360 --> 00:07:19,120
I'm not mad at you.

93
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,960
Why would I be mad?

94
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,000
I'll be back

95
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:28,950
after the work is done.

96
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,911
I'll be back soon.

97
00:07:32,630 --> 00:07:33,920
Xiu'er, you're a big girl now.

98
00:07:34,430 --> 00:07:35,750
You can take care of yourself.

99
00:07:37,560 --> 00:07:38,400
That's right.

100
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,177
I'm a big girl now.

101
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,733
I can take care of myself.

102
00:07:42,390 --> 00:07:44,070
Can I come here often?

103
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:46,670
Of course.

104
00:07:48,070 --> 00:07:49,160
Whenever you want.

105
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,000
This is our home,

106
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:51,840
isn't it?

107
00:07:52,666 --> 00:07:54,155
Whenever you want to come,

108
00:07:54,266 --> 00:07:56,111
ask the Alley Master to bring you.

109
00:07:57,870 --> 00:07:59,240
This is the house

110
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,044
your mother and I used to live in.

111
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,000
Look.

112
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,120
Your mother planted

113
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,630
this osmanthus tree.

114
00:08:07,070 --> 00:08:08,200
It was her favorite.

115
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:13,377
Father, when will you come home?

116
00:08:20,390 --> 00:08:23,390
When the osmanthus tree blooms,

117
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:24,870
I'll be back.

118
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:27,510
That's great.

119
00:08:27,510 --> 00:08:28,822
Then, I'll water it every day

120
00:08:29,120 --> 00:08:30,422
so it'll bloom sooner.

121
00:08:38,380 --> 00:08:41,380
=Episode 15=

122
00:08:52,870 --> 00:08:54,200
Move out!

123
00:09:09,520 --> 00:09:10,220
Yes!

124
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,080
Chief Scribe Zhao,

125
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,870
what's wrong with Lan?

126
00:09:13,244 --> 00:09:14,790
I told him to disrupt the formation,

127
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,666
not to stir them up.

128
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:18,840
Didn't you arrange everything?

129
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:19,680
What's going on now?

130
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,800
He did it on purpose.

131
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,480
He has to put on a show for Li Shande

132
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,720
at the beginning.

133
00:09:53,790 --> 00:09:55,755
Su, you're here
for the court assembly too.

134
00:09:55,955 --> 00:09:57,733
Did you bring some good business here?

135
00:10:00,550 --> 00:10:01,510
Today,

136
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:04,000
I only bring my two ears.

137
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:08,240
Alateng Guxi,

138
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,080
my friend.

139
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,030
Greetings, Mr. Su.

140
00:10:10,030 --> 00:10:11,960
You're the record-keeper today?

141
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:13,320
As before,

142
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,550
if there's anything useful,

143
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,870
I'll write it down word for word.

144
00:10:16,030 --> 00:10:16,870
Very well.

145
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:21,590
Gentlemen,

146
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,160
Ms. Amita is here.

147
00:10:28,550 --> 00:10:30,200
Greetings.

148
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:32,022
Please be seated.

149
00:10:42,270 --> 00:10:43,777
Greetings, everyone.

150
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:46,840
I'm here to ask for some water.

151
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:49,120
May I?

152
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:50,960
Guiyun,

153
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,720
we're holding a court assembly today.

154
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,840
May I ask what brings you here?

155
00:10:55,955 --> 00:10:59,311
A thriving economy brings fortune and
harmony to the nation and its people.

156
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:01,733
This is what Right Chancellor
hopes for.

157
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:05,870
I came here to seek counsel.

158
00:11:06,870 --> 00:11:08,720
If there were ever a venture

159
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:11,390
that could benefit the Tang as well

160
00:11:11,790 --> 00:11:12,790
and yield rich rewards,

161
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:14,600
wouldn't that be wonderful?

162
00:11:14,933 --> 00:11:16,960
It would also make
my inspection mission to Lingnan

163
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,000
worthwhile.

164
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:26,440
If that is so,

165
00:11:27,320 --> 00:11:28,488
please be seated.

166
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,240
Leaders of the association,

167
00:11:47,670 --> 00:11:48,750
the Lingnan Court Assembly

168
00:11:48,910 --> 00:11:50,440
is an important event for us.

169
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:51,910
Last year,

170
00:11:51,910 --> 00:11:52,670
we opened

171
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:53,720
a new trade route,

172
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:55,670
raising profits by twenty percent

173
00:11:55,670 --> 00:11:56,888
from the previous year.

174
00:11:57,360 --> 00:11:59,266
Especially the new trade-in Tazi,

175
00:11:59,510 --> 00:12:00,840
where we exchanged silk and china

176
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,270
for rhino horn, ivory,

177
00:12:02,270 --> 00:12:03,600
spices, and fabrics.

178
00:12:04,120 --> 00:12:04,960
One caravan alone

179
00:12:05,630 --> 00:12:07,600
brought in thirty percent
of the year's profit.

180
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:14,510
This year,

181
00:12:14,510 --> 00:12:16,844
if anyone sees a new,
promising opportunity,

182
00:12:16,870 --> 00:12:17,910
propose it.

183
00:12:18,390 --> 00:12:19,230
House rule.

184
00:12:20,150 --> 00:12:21,320
Whoever proposes the business

185
00:12:21,790 --> 00:12:22,790
shall lead it.

186
00:12:23,022 --> 00:12:24,200
If the proposal is approved,

187
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,866
everyone invests,
and we profit together.

188
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:29,320
Aye, aye!

189
00:12:35,488 --> 00:12:37,200
Why are they handing out sweets first?

190
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,560
They're not sweets.

191
00:12:39,866 --> 00:12:41,870
It's the usual practice
at the court assembly.

192
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:43,870
Everyone receives two pieces of ox bone.

193
00:12:44,044 --> 00:12:45,480
They look the same on the outside,

194
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:46,870
but one is hollow,

195
00:12:46,870 --> 00:12:47,910
and the other is solid.

196
00:12:48,120 --> 00:12:49,240
Only the person holding it

197
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,080
can tell.

198
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:52,030
Solid means agree,

199
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,670
and hollow means disagree.

200
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:55,360
Then, each person drops the one

201
00:12:55,360 --> 00:12:56,840
that reflects their vote

202
00:12:56,840 --> 00:12:57,910
into the box

203
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,120
and the other

204
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,266
into a second box.

205
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:01,630
I see.

206
00:13:01,630 --> 00:13:02,480
So no one knows

207
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:03,390
who agrees

208
00:13:03,390 --> 00:13:04,440
or disagrees.

209
00:13:05,550 --> 00:13:06,390
Interesting.

210
00:13:06,630 --> 00:13:07,480
Of course.

211
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:08,840
It was Ms. Amita's idea.

212
00:13:09,777 --> 00:13:11,466
Now the ox bones have been distributed,

213
00:13:11,910 --> 00:13:14,390
so let the court assembly begin.

214
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:01,840
Hollow.

215
00:14:03,270 --> 00:14:04,110
Hollow.

216
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:10,666
Ms. Amita, the proposal wasn't approved.

217
00:14:12,066 --> 00:14:14,111
I've been sitting here
watching this whole time.

218
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:15,390
None of the proposals

219
00:14:15,390 --> 00:14:16,720
has been accepted.

220
00:14:17,288 --> 00:14:18,622
Right Chancellor has given us

221
00:14:18,666 --> 00:14:19,666
every advantage,

222
00:14:20,030 --> 00:14:21,711
yet everyone is still so cautious.

223
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,333
How can the association progress?

224
00:14:23,377 --> 00:14:24,933
If Right Chancellor heard this,

225
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,670
he would surely be worried.

226
00:14:27,177 --> 00:14:29,311
Good business opportunities
are always out there.

227
00:14:29,840 --> 00:14:31,720
All it takes is a keen eye to discover

228
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,733
and a bold spirit to act on them.

229
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:35,630
I have a suggestion.

230
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,440
Since we opened

231
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:39,510
the trade route with Tazi last year,

232
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:40,440
why not

233
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,600
expand it further?

234
00:14:42,390 --> 00:14:44,440
Now, the Tang's china, tea leaves,

235
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,550
silk, and paper

236
00:14:45,550 --> 00:14:47,440
are in high demand in Tazi.

237
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:50,000
This way, we could bring back

238
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:52,630
more ivory, rhino horn, and spices

239
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,720
to further expand our business

240
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:57,200
and break last year's profit record.

241
00:14:57,510 --> 00:14:58,350
Brilliant!

242
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:00,320
Break the record.

243
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,150
It sounds like a good idea.

244
00:15:03,790 --> 00:15:05,480
Let's all stop voting

245
00:15:05,480 --> 00:15:06,480
with hollow bones.

246
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:11,150
Last year, when Ms. Amita proposed

247
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:12,790
the business route to Tazi,

248
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,750
none of us approved of it.

249
00:15:15,270 --> 00:15:16,600
If not

250
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:18,360
for her sharp judgment
and decisive call,

251
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,510
how would we

252
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:22,840
have today's abundant profits?

253
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:24,870
Since Ms. Amita

254
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,670
has faith in this project,

255
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:29,840
let's vote.

256
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:32,560
Faqi.

257
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,080
Take out your abacus

258
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,088
and do the math.

259
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:45,320
Tell me,

260
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,360
when you traveled alone

261
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,120
across the sea and back,

262
00:15:49,840 --> 00:15:51,600
how much profit did you make each year?

263
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:55,150
You said Ms. Amita has sharp judgment.

264
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:56,510
That's true.

265
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:57,670
These past years,

266
00:15:57,670 --> 00:15:59,270
our business has been thriving,

267
00:16:00,510 --> 00:16:03,440
but the money

268
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:06,480
actually going into our pockets,
has it increased

269
00:16:08,910 --> 00:16:09,750
or decreased?

270
00:16:12,510 --> 00:16:13,550
Based on what you've said,

271
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,790
business is booming,

272
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,630
but the money

273
00:16:17,630 --> 00:16:19,000
has become less.

274
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,390
You said that on purpose.

275
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:23,720
I have a feeling you're a traitor.

276
00:16:23,977 --> 00:16:27,222
You bite the hand that feeds you and
turn your back on those who help you.

277
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:35,710
Mr. Ma,

278
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:38,555
how could I bite a feeding hand

279
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:40,440
if it never existed?

280
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:42,866
Who could I turn against

281
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:44,670
if no one ever helped me?

282
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:48,720
Mr. Ma, you may not be aware.

283
00:16:49,030 --> 00:16:51,550
Pirates have been running amok
these years.

284
00:16:51,870 --> 00:16:54,360
They constantly attack merchant ships.

285
00:16:54,790 --> 00:16:55,630
Out of desperation,

286
00:16:55,870 --> 00:16:57,200
we Hu merchants have no choice

287
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,960
but to pay with our own money

288
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:03,311
to ransom our ships and cargo.

289
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:06,790
Mr. Fan, your Yonghe Store
suffered losses

290
00:17:07,510 --> 00:17:08,920
because of this.

291
00:17:10,240 --> 00:17:11,080
Mr. Gu,

292
00:17:12,110 --> 00:17:14,070
I believe that's when

293
00:17:14,070 --> 00:17:16,155
you changed your line of business.

294
00:17:17,030 --> 00:17:20,070
I'm not making baseless claims, am I?

295
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,350
All these profitable ventures
these years

296
00:17:25,350 --> 00:17:26,400
came from my proposals.

297
00:17:26,550 --> 00:17:28,200
And now you're stirring trouble here...

298
00:17:28,577 --> 00:17:30,044
What's your real intention?

299
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,350
Do you have

300
00:17:32,550 --> 00:17:33,880
an even more profitable business

301
00:17:34,310 --> 00:17:35,240
to share with us?

302
00:17:36,310 --> 00:17:37,160
Of course I do.

303
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,000
As you all know,

304
00:17:40,590 --> 00:17:43,720
the Litchi Envoy is currently running
a trial of litchi delivery

305
00:17:43,720 --> 00:17:45,070
at the East Gate.

306
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:48,030
If you will lend a hand,

307
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:49,240
once it succeeds,

308
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:54,070
profits could exceed thirty percent.

309
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:58,160
